[D7]How silent it seems here [G]today
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 5}
[D7]There's an old rail fence that [C]we built inch by [G]inch
[A7]Surrounding the old family [D7]graves
[G]And there's one gravestone [C]standing all [G]alone
[D7]There waiting to join me in the [G]shade
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 6}
[C]Tall pines tall pines
[G]Reaching up for the [D7]clouds
[G]Tall pines tall [C]pines
